Coming up on @realmoney In A Richly-Valued Market Bank Stocks Represent Uncommon Value Under Almost Any Time Frame * Bank stocks represent the best intermediate term value in the markets (of any S&P sector). * Most of the downside in interest rates and in the flattening of the

yield curve is now likely behind us. * Banks are rate/asset sensitive - they prosper when rates rise and the yield curve steepens. * The near term rate risk is now behind us and bank stocks seem less vulnerable (over the near term) even if the overall stock market falters.
* Look through the windshield and not in the rear view mirror. @jimcramer @tomkeene @TeamCavuto @SquawkCNBC @carlquintanilla @andrewrsorkin @cnbcfastmoney @saraeisen @michaelsantoli
